  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Book Clubs in Secondary Schools across Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Poverty and high cost of books have been identified as reasons for the poor reading culture in public secondary schools across Nigeria. This project is critical to bridging the gap. It will create and monitor book clubs in 100 public secondary schools in Nigeria, providing them with a rich supply of books. It will impact about 10,000 pupils from low-income families across Nigeria by improving their critical thinking  and reading skills and consequently improving their socio-economic prospects.</narrative>
  </description>
